# Hoppity — LLM Code Generation Reference

Pattern-driven RabbitMQ topology builder for Node.js microservices, built on Rascal.

## Package Overview

| Package | npm Name | Version | Status | Dependencies |
|---------|----------|---------|--------|--------------|
| hoppity | `@apogeelabs/hoppity` | 0.2.0 | Stable | `rascal@^20.1.1`, `fast-deep-equal@^3.1.3` |
| hoppity-rpc | `@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc` | 0.2.0 | Stable | `@apogeelabs/hoppity` (workspace), `rascal@^20.1.1` (peer) |
| hoppity-delayed-publish | `@apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish` | 0.2.0 | Stable | `@apogeelabs/hoppity` (workspace), `rascal@^20.1.1` (peer) |
| hoppity-subscriptions | `@apogeelabs/hoppity-subscriptions` | 0.2.0 | Stable | `@apogeelabs/hoppity` (workspace), `rascal@^20.1.1` (peer) |
| hoppity-logger | `@apogeelabs/hoppity-logger` | 0.2.0 | Stable | `@apogeelabs/hoppity` (workspace), `rascal@^20.1.1` (peer) |

All packages require Node >= 22. All produce CJS, ESM, and type declarations.

## Type Signatures

### Core Types (`@apogeelabs/hoppity`)

```typescript
import { BrokerConfig, BrokerAsPromised, PublicationConfig } from "rascal";

// Logger interface — all middleware and packages use this
interface Logger {
    silly(message: string, ...args: any[]): void;
    debug(message: string, ...args: any[]): void;
    info(message: string, ...args: any[]): void;
    warn(message: string, ...args: any[]): void;
    error(message: string, ...args: any[]): void;
    critical(message: string, ...args: any[]): void;
}

// Shared state passed through the middleware pipeline
interface MiddlewareContext {
    data: Record<string, any>;      // Mutable shared state for inter-middleware communication
    middlewareNames: string[];       // Names of all executed middleware (in order)
    logger: Logger;                  // Logger instance (defaults to ConsoleLogger)
}

// What every middleware function must return
interface MiddlewareResult {
    topology: BrokerConfig;                                       // Modified topology (required)
    onBrokerCreated?: (broker: BrokerAsPromised) => void | Promise<void>;  // Optional lifecycle hook
}

// The middleware function signature
type MiddlewareFunction = (
    topology: BrokerConfig,
    context: MiddlewareContext
) => MiddlewareResult;

// Alias for the onBrokerCreated callback
type BrokerCreatedCallback = (broker: BrokerAsPromised) => void | Promise<void>;

// The fluent builder API returned by withTopology() and use()
interface BuilderInterface {
    use(middleware: MiddlewareFunction): BuilderInterface;
    build(): Promise<BrokerAsPromised>;
}

// Utility type for extending broker with custom methods (used by RPC, delayed-publish)
type BrokerWithExtensions<T extends Record<string, any>[]> =
    BrokerAsPromised & UnionToIntersection<T[number]>;

// (Internal utility — included for completeness)
type UnionToIntersection<U> = (U extends any ? (k: U) => void : never) extends (k: infer I) => void
    ? I
    : never;
```

### RPC Types (`@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc`)

```typescript
interface RpcMiddlewareOptions {
    serviceName: string;          // Used for queue naming and routing
    instanceId: string;           // Unique per service instance
    rpcExchange?: string;         // Defaults to "rpc_requests"
    defaultTimeout?: number;      // Defaults to 30_000 ms
}

interface RpcRequest {
    correlationId: string;
    rpcName: string;
    payload: any;
    replyTo: string;
    headers?: Record<string, any>;
}

interface RpcResponse {
    correlationId: string;
    payload?: any;
    error?: {
        code: string;
        message: string;
        details?: any;
    };
    headers?: Record<string, any>;
}

// Extended broker interface after withRpcSupport middleware runs
interface RpcBroker extends BrokerAsPromised {
    request<TRequest = any, TResponse = any>(
        rpcName: string,
        message: TRequest,
        overrides?: PublicationConfig
    ): Promise<TResponse>;

    addRpcListener<TRequest = any, TResponse = any>(
        rpcName: string,
        handler: (request: TRequest) => Promise<TResponse>
    ): void;

    cancelRequest(correlationId: string): boolean;
}

enum RpcErrorCode {
    TIMEOUT = "RPC_TIMEOUT",
    METHOD_NOT_FOUND = "RPC_METHOD_NOT_FOUND",
    HANDLER_ERROR = "RPC_HANDLER_ERROR",
    CANCELLED = "RPC_CANCELLED",
    SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE = "RPC_SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE",
}
```

### Delayed Publish Types (`@apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish`)

```typescript
interface DelayedPublishOptions {
    serviceName: string;          // Used for queue naming
    instanceId: string;           // Unique per service instance
    defaultDelay?: number;        // Defaults to 30_000 ms
    maxRetries?: number;          // Defaults to 5
    retryDelay?: number;          // Defaults to 1_000 ms
    durable?: boolean;            // Defaults to true — controls queue durability and message persistence
}

interface DelayedMessage {
    originalMessage: any;
    originalPublication: string;
    originalOverrides?: PublicationConfig;
    targetDelay: number;
    createdAt: number;
    retryCount?: number;
}

// Extended broker interface after withDelayedPublish middleware runs
interface DelayedPublishBroker extends BrokerAsPromised {
    delayedPublish(
        publication: string,
        message: any,
        overrides?: PublicationConfig,
        delay?: number               // Uses defaultDelay if omitted
    ): Promise<void>;
}

enum DelayedPublishErrorCode {
    QUEUE_FULL = "DELAYED_PUBLISH_QUEUE_FULL",
    REPUBLISH_FAILED = "DELAYED_PUBLISH_REPUBLISH_FAILED",
    MAX_RETRIES_EXCEEDED = "DELAYED_PUBLISH_MAX_RETRIES_EXCEEDED",
    INVALID_DELAY = "DELAYED_PUBLISH_INVALID_DELAY",
}

class DelayedPublishError extends Error {
    public readonly code: DelayedPublishErrorCode;
    public readonly details?: any;
    constructor(code: DelayedPublishErrorCode, message: string, details?: any);
}
```

### Subscriptions Types (`@apogeelabs/hoppity-subscriptions`)

```typescript
// Handler receives the raw Rascal message, parsed content, ack/nack function, and broker
type SubscriptionHandler = (
    message: any,                                        // Rascal message object
    content: any,                                        // Parsed message content
    ackOrNackFn: (err?: Error, recovery?: any) => void,  // Acknowledge or reject
    broker: BrokerAsPromised                             // Broker instance
) => Promise<void> | void;

// Map of subscription names to handler functions
type SubscriptionHandlers = Record<string, SubscriptionHandler>;

interface ValidationResult {
    isValid: boolean;
    missingSubscriptions: string[];       // Handler keys with no matching subscription in topology
    availableSubscriptions: string[];     // Subscription names found in topology
    invalidHandlers: string[];            // Handler keys that are not functions
    errorMessage?: string;
}
```

### Logger Types (`@apogeelabs/hoppity-logger`)

```typescript
interface WithCustomLoggerOptions {
    logger: Logger;   // Any object implementing the Logger interface
}
```

## Function Signatures

### `@apogeelabs/hoppity`

```typescript
// Default export — the entry point
const hoppity: {
    withTopology(topology: BrokerConfig): BuilderInterface;
    use(middleware: MiddlewareFunction): BuilderInterface;
};

// Named exports
class ConsoleLogger implements Logger { /* all 6 log methods */ }
const defaultLogger: ConsoleLogger;  // Singleton instance
```

### `@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc`

```typescript
function withRpcSupport(options: RpcMiddlewareOptions): MiddlewareFunction;
```

### `@apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish`

```typescript
function withDelayedPublish(options: DelayedPublishOptions): MiddlewareFunction;
```

### `@apogeelabs/hoppity-subscriptions`

```typescript
function withSubscriptions(handlers: SubscriptionHandlers): MiddlewareFunction;
function validateSubscriptionHandlers(
    topology: BrokerConfig,
    handlers: SubscriptionHandlers
): ValidationResult;
```

### `@apogeelabs/hoppity-logger`

```typescript
function withCustomLogger(options: WithCustomLoggerOptions): MiddlewareFunction;
```

## Per-Function Usage Examples

### hoppity — `withTopology` + `use` + `build`

```typescript
import hoppity from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import { BrokerConfig } from "rascal";

const topology: BrokerConfig = {
    vhosts: {
        "/": {
            connection: {
                hostname: "localhost",
                user: "guest",
                password: "guest",
                port: 5672,
                vhost: "/",
            },
            exchanges: {
                events: { type: "topic" },
            },
            queues: {
                event_queue: {},
            },
            bindings: {
                event_binding: {
                    source: "events",
                    destination: "event_queue",
                    bindingKey: "event.#",
                },
            },
            publications: {
                publish_event: {
                    exchange: "events",
                    routingKey: "event.created",
                },
            },
            subscriptions: {
                on_event: {
                    queue: "event_queue",
                    prefetch: 1,
                },
            },
        },
    },
};

const broker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(topology)
    .use(someMiddleware)
    .build();
```

### hoppity — Starting without initial topology

```typescript
// You can also start with .use() directly (topology defaults to {})
const broker = await hoppity
    .use(middlewareThatSetsUpTopology)
    .use(anotherMiddleware)
    .build();
```

### withRpcSupport

```typescript
import hoppity from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import { withRpcSupport, RpcBroker } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc";
import { randomUUID } from "crypto";

const broker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(baseTopology)
    .use(
        withRpcSupport({
            serviceName: "order-service",
            instanceId: randomUUID(),
            rpcExchange: "rpc_requests",
            defaultTimeout: 15_000,
        })
    )
    .build() as RpcBroker;

// Register an RPC handler
broker.addRpcListener<{ orderId: string }, { status: string }>(
    "order-service.getStatus",
    async (request) => {
        return { status: "shipped" };
    }
);

// Make an RPC request to another service
const result = await broker.request<{ userId: string }, { name: string }>(
    "user-service.getProfile",
    { userId: "123" }
);
```

### withDelayedPublish

```typescript
import hoppity from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import { withDelayedPublish, DelayedPublishBroker } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish";
import { randomUUID } from "crypto";

const broker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(baseTopology)
    .use(
        withDelayedPublish({
            serviceName: "notification-service",
            instanceId: randomUUID(),
            defaultDelay: 30_000,
            maxRetries: 5,
            retryDelay: 1_000,
        })
    )
    .build() as DelayedPublishBroker;

// Publish with explicit 5-second delay
await broker.delayedPublish("send_notification", { userId: "123" }, undefined, 5_000);

// Publish with default delay (30 seconds)
await broker.delayedPublish("send_reminder", { userId: "456" });
```

### withSubscriptions

```typescript
import hoppity from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import { withSubscriptions, SubscriptionHandler } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-subscriptions";

const onOrderCreated: SubscriptionHandler = async (message, content, ackOrNack, broker) => {
    try {
        console.log("Order received:", content);
        ackOrNack(); // Acknowledge
    } catch (err) {
        ackOrNack(err as Error); // Reject
    }
};

const broker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(topology) // topology must have a subscription named "on_order_created"
    .use(
        withSubscriptions({
            on_order_created: onOrderCreated,
        })
    )
    .build();
```

### validateSubscriptionHandlers (standalone validation)

```typescript
import { validateSubscriptionHandlers } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-subscriptions";

const result = validateSubscriptionHandlers(topology, {
    on_order_created: handler1,
    on_nonexistent: handler2,
});

if (!result.isValid) {
    console.error(result.errorMessage);
    // "Subscription validation failed: Missing subscriptions: on_nonexistent. Available subscriptions: on_order_created"
}
```

### withCustomLogger

```typescript
import hoppity from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import { withCustomLogger, Logger } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-logger";
import winston from "winston";

// Wrap Winston to match the Logger interface
const winstonLogger = winston.createLogger({
    level: "info",
    format: winston.format.json(),
    transports: [new winston.transports.Console()],
});

const logger: Logger = {
    silly: (msg, ...args) => winstonLogger.silly(msg, ...args),
    debug: (msg, ...args) => winstonLogger.debug(msg, ...args),
    info: (msg, ...args) => winstonLogger.info(msg, ...args),
    warn: (msg, ...args) => winstonLogger.warn(msg, ...args),
    error: (msg, ...args) => winstonLogger.error(msg, ...args),
    critical: (msg, ...args) => winstonLogger.error(msg, ...args), // Winston has no "critical"
};

// Apply FIRST so downstream middleware can use it
const broker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(topology)
    .use(withCustomLogger({ logger }))
    .use(withRpcSupport({ serviceName: "my-svc", instanceId: "abc" }))
    .build();
```

## Writing Custom Middleware

### Middleware Function Signature

```typescript
import { MiddlewareFunction, MiddlewareResult, MiddlewareContext } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import { BrokerConfig, BrokerAsPromised } from "rascal";

const myMiddleware: MiddlewareFunction = (
    topology: BrokerConfig,
    context: MiddlewareContext
): MiddlewareResult => {
    // 1. Read/modify topology
    const modified = structuredClone(topology);
    modified.vhosts ??= {};
    modified.vhosts["/"] ??= {};
    modified.vhosts["/"].exchanges ??= {};
    modified.vhosts["/"].exchanges["my-exchange"] = { type: "topic" };

    // 2. Share data with downstream middleware via context.data
    context.data.myConfig = { exchangeName: "my-exchange" };

    // 3. Use the logger
    context.logger.info("My middleware executed");

    // 4. Return modified topology + optional lifecycle hook
    return {
        topology: modified,
        onBrokerCreated: async (broker: BrokerAsPromised) => {
            // Runs AFTER broker is created, BEFORE build() resolves
            const sub = await broker.subscribe("my-subscription");
            sub.on("message", (msg, content, ackOrNack) => {
                // handle messages
                ackOrNack();
            });
        },
    };
};
```

### Middleware Factory Pattern (parameterized middleware)

```typescript
interface MyMiddlewareOptions {
    exchangeName: string;
    routingKey: string;
}

function withMyFeature(options: MyMiddlewareOptions): MiddlewareFunction {
    return (topology: BrokerConfig, context: MiddlewareContext): MiddlewareResult => {
        const modified = structuredClone(topology);
        // ... modify topology using options ...
        return {
            topology: modified,
            onBrokerCreated: async (broker) => {
                // ... setup using options and broker ...
            },
        };
    };
}

// Usage
const broker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(base)
    .use(withMyFeature({ exchangeName: "events", routingKey: "event.#" }))
    .build();
```

### Middleware Lifecycle

1. All middleware functions execute **sequentially** during `.build()`
2. Each receives the **cumulative** topology (modified by all prior middleware)
3. `context` is **shared** — mutations to `context.data` are visible downstream
4. `onBrokerCreated` callbacks execute **sequentially after** broker creation
5. If a callback fails, the broker is **shut down** before the error propagates

## Canonical Examples

### Example 1: Basic Pub/Sub with Custom Logger and Subscriptions

```typescript
import hoppity, { MiddlewareContext } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import { withCustomLogger } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-logger";
import { withSubscriptions, SubscriptionHandler } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-subscriptions";
import { BrokerConfig, BrokerAsPromised } from "rascal";

const topology: BrokerConfig = {
    vhosts: {
        "/": {
            connection: {
                hostname: "localhost",
                user: "guest",
                password: "guest",
                port: 5672,
                vhost: "/",
            },
            exchanges: {
                events: { type: "topic" },
            },
            queues: {
                event_queue: {},
            },
            bindings: {
                event_binding: {
                    source: "events",
                    destination: "event_queue",
                    bindingKey: "event.#",
                },
            },
            publications: {
                publish_event: {
                    exchange: "events",
                    routingKey: "event.created",
                },
            },
            subscriptions: {
                on_event: {
                    queue: "event_queue",
                    prefetch: 1,
                },
            },
        },
    },
};

const handleEvent: SubscriptionHandler = async (message, content, ackOrNack, broker) => {
    console.log("Received event:", content);
    ackOrNack();
};

const broker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(topology)
    .use(withCustomLogger({ logger: myLogger }))
    .use(withSubscriptions({ on_event: handleEvent }))
    .build();

// Publish a message
const publication = await broker.publish("publish_event", { type: "user.created", userId: "123" });
publication.on("error", console.error);

// Graceful shutdown
process.on("SIGTERM", async () => {
    await broker.shutdown();
});
```

### Example 2: RPC Between Two Services

```typescript
// --- Handler Service ---
import hoppity from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import { withRpcSupport, RpcBroker } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc";
import { randomUUID } from "crypto";

const handlerBroker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(baseTopology)
    .use(
        withRpcSupport({
            serviceName: "user-service",
            instanceId: randomUUID(),
        })
    )
    .build() as RpcBroker;

handlerBroker.addRpcListener<{ userId: string }, { name: string; email: string }>(
    "user-service.getProfile",
    async (request) => {
        // Look up user by ID
        return { name: "Jane Doe", email: "jane@example.com" };
    }
);

// --- Requester Service ---
const requesterBroker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(baseTopology)
    .use(
        withRpcSupport({
            serviceName: "api-gateway",
            instanceId: randomUUID(),
        })
    )
    .build() as RpcBroker;

const profile = await requesterBroker.request<{ userId: string }, { name: string; email: string }>(
    "user-service.getProfile",
    { userId: "42" }
);
console.log(profile.name); // "Jane Doe"
```

### Example 3: Delayed Publishing with Retry

```typescript
import hoppity from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import { withDelayedPublish, DelayedPublishBroker } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish";
import { withSubscriptions, SubscriptionHandler } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-subscriptions";
import { withCustomLogger } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-logger";
import { randomUUID } from "crypto";

const handleNotification: SubscriptionHandler = async (message, content, ackOrNack) => {
    console.log("Sending notification:", content);
    ackOrNack();
};

const broker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(topology)
    .use(withCustomLogger({ logger: myLogger }))
    .use(
        withDelayedPublish({
            serviceName: "notification-svc",
            instanceId: randomUUID(),
            defaultDelay: 60_000,     // 1 minute default delay
            maxRetries: 3,
            retryDelay: 2_000,
        })
    )
    .use(withSubscriptions({ on_notification: handleNotification }))
    .build() as DelayedPublishBroker;

// Schedule a notification for 5 minutes from now
await broker.delayedPublish(
    "send_notification",
    { userId: "123", message: "Your order has shipped!" },
    undefined,
    300_000
);
```

### Example 4: Composing All Middleware

```typescript
import hoppity from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import { withCustomLogger } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-logger";
import { withRpcSupport, RpcBroker } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc";
import { withDelayedPublish, DelayedPublishBroker } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish";
import { withSubscriptions } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-subscriptions";
import { randomUUID } from "crypto";

const broker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(topology)
    .use(withCustomLogger({ logger }))            // 1. Logger first
    .use(withRpcSupport({                          // 2. RPC support
        serviceName: "order-service",
        instanceId: randomUUID(),
    }))
    .use(withDelayedPublish({                      // 3. Delayed publish
        serviceName: "order-service",
        instanceId: randomUUID(),
    }))
    .use(withSubscriptions({                       // 4. Subscriptions last
        on_order_created: handleOrder,
    }))
    .build() as RpcBroker & DelayedPublishBroker;

// Now broker has .request(), .addRpcListener(), and .delayedPublish()
```

## Common Mistakes / Do NOT Do This

### Wrong: Importing from sub-paths

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG — no deep imports exist
import { RascalBuilder } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity/dist/RascalBuilder";
import { setupRpcBroker } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc/dist/setupRpcBroker";
import { handleReadyMessage } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish/dist/handleReadyMessage";

// ✅ CORRECT — always import from package root
import hoppity from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import { withRpcSupport } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc";
import { withDelayedPublish } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish";
```

### Wrong: Using `hoppity` as a constructor

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG — hoppity is a plain object, not a class
const builder = new hoppity();
const builder = new Hoppity();

// ✅ CORRECT — use the static methods
const builder = hoppity.withTopology(config);
const builder = hoppity.use(middleware);
```

### Wrong: Returning Promise from middleware function

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG — middleware functions are synchronous
const myMiddleware: MiddlewareFunction = async (topology, context) => {
    const data = await fetchSomething(); // NO async in middleware body
    return { topology };
};

// ✅ CORRECT — do async work in onBrokerCreated
const myMiddleware: MiddlewareFunction = (topology, context) => {
    return {
        topology,
        onBrokerCreated: async (broker) => {
            const data = await fetchSomething(); // Async work goes here
        },
    };
};
```

### Wrong: Mutating topology in-place

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG — don't mutate the received topology object
const myMiddleware: MiddlewareFunction = (topology, context) => {
    topology.vhosts["/"].exchanges["new"] = { type: "topic" }; // Mutation!
    return { topology };
};

// ✅ CORRECT — clone first, then modify
const myMiddleware: MiddlewareFunction = (topology, context) => {
    const modified = structuredClone(topology);
    modified.vhosts ??= {};
    modified.vhosts["/"] ??= {};
    modified.vhosts["/"].exchanges ??= {};
    modified.vhosts["/"].exchanges["new"] = { type: "topic" };
    return { topology: modified };
};
```

### Wrong: Forgetting `.build()`

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG — this is a BuilderInterface, not a broker
const broker = hoppity.withTopology(topology).use(middleware);
await broker.publish("foo", {}); // TypeError: broker.publish is not a function

// ✅ CORRECT — call .build() to get the broker
const broker = await hoppity.withTopology(topology).use(middleware).build();
await broker.publish("foo", {});
```

### Wrong: Accessing broker methods without casting

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG — TypeScript won't know about .request() or .delayedPublish()
const broker = await hoppity.withTopology(t).use(withRpcSupport(opts)).build();
broker.request("foo", {}); // Property 'request' does not exist

// ✅ CORRECT — cast to the extended broker type
const broker = await hoppity.withTopology(t).use(withRpcSupport(opts)).build() as RpcBroker;
broker.request("foo", {});

// Or for multiple middleware:
const broker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(t)
    .use(withRpcSupport(opts))
    .use(withDelayedPublish(opts2))
    .build() as RpcBroker & DelayedPublishBroker;
```

### Wrong: Putting withCustomLogger after other middleware

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG — middleware before withCustomLogger won't use the custom logger
const broker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(topology)
    .use(withRpcSupport(opts))         // Uses default ConsoleLogger
    .use(withCustomLogger({ logger })) // Too late for RPC middleware
    .build();

// ✅ CORRECT — logger first
const broker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(topology)
    .use(withCustomLogger({ logger })) // All subsequent middleware use this logger
    .use(withRpcSupport(opts))
    .build();
```

### Wrong: Subscription handler key doesn't match topology

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG — handler key must exactly match a subscription name in the topology
const broker = await hoppity
    .withTopology(topology) // has subscription named "on_order_created"
    .use(withSubscriptions({
        order_created: handler, // Wrong key! Should be "on_order_created"
    }))
    .build();
// Error: "Subscription validation failed: Missing subscriptions: order_created"

// ✅ CORRECT — key matches exactly
    .use(withSubscriptions({
        on_order_created: handler,
    }))
```

### Wrong: SubscriptionHandler with wrong argument count

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG — missing the broker (4th argument)
const handler: SubscriptionHandler = (message, content, ackOrNack) => {
    // Missing broker parameter
};

// ✅ CORRECT — all 4 parameters
const handler: SubscriptionHandler = (message, content, ackOrNack, broker) => {
    ackOrNack();
};
```

### Wrong: Not handling errors in subscription handlers

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG — unhandled error will nack with default behavior
const handler: SubscriptionHandler = async (message, content, ackOrNack, broker) => {
    const result = await processOrder(content); // If this throws, message is nacked
    // but you get no control over the error response
};

// ✅ CORRECT — explicit error handling
const handler: SubscriptionHandler = async (message, content, ackOrNack, broker) => {
    try {
        const result = await processOrder(content);
        ackOrNack();
    } catch (err) {
        console.error("Failed to process:", err);
        ackOrNack(err as Error, { strategy: "nack", requeue: false });
    }
};
```

## Complete Import Reference

Every valid import path — there are **NO deep import paths**.

```typescript
// @apogeelabs/hoppity
import hoppity from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";                          // Default: builder entry point
import type { MiddlewareFunction } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import type { MiddlewareContext } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import type { MiddlewareResult } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import type { BuilderInterface } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import type { BrokerCreatedCallback } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import type { BrokerWithExtensions } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import type { Hoppity } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import type { Logger } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import { ConsoleLogger } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";
import { defaultLogger } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity";

// @apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc
import { withRpcSupport } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc";
import { RpcErrorCode } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc";
import type { RpcMiddlewareOptions } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc";
import type { RpcRequest } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc";
import type { RpcResponse } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc";
import type { RpcBroker } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc";
import type { Logger } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-rpc";              // Re-exported from core

// @apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish
import { withDelayedPublish } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish";
import { DelayedPublishError } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish";
import { DelayedPublishErrorCode } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish";
import type { DelayedPublishOptions } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish";
import type { DelayedMessage } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish";
import type { DelayedPublishBroker } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-delayed-publish";

// @apogeelabs/hoppity-subscriptions
import { withSubscriptions } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-subscriptions";
import { validateSubscriptionHandlers } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-subscriptions";
import type { SubscriptionHandler } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-subscriptions";
import type { SubscriptionHandlers } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-subscriptions";
import type { ValidationResult } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-subscriptions";

// @apogeelabs/hoppity-logger
import { withCustomLogger } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-logger";
import type { WithCustomLoggerOptions } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-logger";
import type { Logger } from "@apogeelabs/hoppity-logger";           // Re-exported from core
```

⚠️ There are **NO** other valid import paths. Do not attempt to import from `dist/`, sub-modules, or internal files.

## Established Patterns

### Singleton Broker Pattern

Each service typically creates one broker instance and reuses it:

```typescript
let brokerInstance: BrokerAsPromised | null = null;

export async function getBroker(): Promise<BrokerAsPromised> {
    if (brokerInstance) return brokerInstance;
    brokerInstance = await hoppity.withTopology(topology).use(middleware).build();
    return brokerInstance;
}
```

### Graceful Shutdown

```typescript
async function shutdown(broker: BrokerAsPromised): Promise<void> {
    await broker.shutdown();
    process.exit(0);
}

process.on("SIGTERM", () => shutdown(broker));
process.on("SIGINT", () => shutdown(broker));
```

### Topology Separation

Define topology in a dedicated file, separate from broker creation:

```typescript
// messaging/topology.ts
export const topology: BrokerConfig = { /* ... */ };

// messaging/broker.ts
import { topology } from "./topology";
export async function createBroker() {
    return hoppity.withTopology(topology).use(...).build();
}
```

### Middleware Ordering Convention

```
1. withCustomLogger       — Logger first (so all others can use it)
2. withRpcSupport         — Topology additions
3. withDelayedPublish     — Topology additions
4. withSubscriptions      — Validates + wires (should be last, after topology is finalized)
5. Custom middleware       — Your own middleware, ordered by dependency
```
